NAME: Jamar Nicholson
OFFICER: PO II Miguel Gutierrez, Serial No. 36634
ACCOUNT: Jamar Nicholson, a 15-year-old Black youth who had stopped with friends in an alley on the way to school. He had been rapping and dancing with his friends, which they later explained was part of their routine before school. Offer Miguel Gutierrez shot into the group and hit Jamar in the shoulder.
Address:
10th Avenue and Florence Avenue in Los Angeles,
CA, a few blocks from their high school

NAME: Redel Kentel Jones
OFFICER: PO II Brett Ramirez, Serial No. 41223
ACCOUNT: Redel Jones was a 29-year-old Black disabled woman who was killed by police across from the Crenshaw Mall.

NAME: Keith Bursey Jr
ACCOUNT: Keith Bursey was 31 years old when he was murdered by LAPD Gang Officer on June 10th, 2016. He was stopped for a search when Officer Kumlander took his life. Keith Bursey was a beloved son, brother, and father. He’s remembered for his athletic ability, his love of dance, and his disarming humor.

NAME: Gilbert Henry
ACCOUNT: Gilbert Henry is a Black man who was shot in a LASER zone by Metro Division officers who “attempted to detain [him] for drinking in public.”

NAME: Grechario Mack
OFFICER: Ryan Lee + Martin Robles, Serial No. 36603 / 41225
ACCOUNT: Grechario Mack was 30 years old when was murdered by two LAPD officers on April 10th, 2018. He was hunted and shot multiple times, including while he was on ground and in his back during a mental health episode. While the Police Commision ruled the murder “out of policy," Chief Moore reminds us that this is exactly what pigs do.
Address: 3650 W. Martin Luther King Jr. Blvd.

NAME: Jose Juan Mendez
ACCOUNT: José Juan Méndez was killed by Hollenbeck Division patrol officers Josue Merida and Jeremy Wagner during a traffic stop in what LAPD designated as the Estrada CLEAR area, a “problem area” and a LASER zone. He was 16 years old.

NAME: Robert Mark Diaz
ACCOUNT: Robert Mark Diaz was 28 years old when he was killed by LAPD GED Officer Miguel Ruano on May 13th, 2016. Officer Ruano fired multiple shots into Diaz’s head after straddling his leg and gaining control of him. Robert is remembered for his ability to defuse tense situations with his warmth and his love of animals.

NAME: Richard Risher
ACCOUNT: Richard Risher was killed by officers Francisco Zaragoza, Isaac Fernandez, and Joseph Chavez inside a LASER zone. He was 18 years old. The cops shot him in the back.

NAME: Jesse Romero
ACCOUNT: Jesse Romero was 14 years old when he was shot in the back by LAPD GED Officer Eden Medina in a LASER zone in Boyle Heights, where he was constantly harassed by the gang unit. Officer Medina had murdered another individual just twelve days prior. Jesse’s legacy is maintained by his father who continues to champion the fight for justice in the name of his son.
Address: 2200 block of East Cesar E. Chavez Avenue

NAME: Kenney Watkins
ACCOUNT: Kenney Watkins was killed in a LASER Zone by LAPD officer Evan Urias who claimed he was making a traffic stop for a missing front plate, tinted windows, and “possibly a paper back plate.” Urias shot him in the back.

NAME: Daniel Perez
ACCOUNT: Daniel Perez was killed by Newton Division GED officer Ian Chessum who was on patrol in a Newton CLEAR area, which was also a LASER Zone. He was 16 years old when killed by police looking for a “man with a gun.”
